- 'Golden age of 'O(n log n)' represents algorithms with an order of growth of 'O(n log n)';
- 'Beacons in the wilderness of industry standards' stands for benchmarks that are industry standards;
- 'Crucible of production environments' refers to the run environment in production;
- 'Twilight threshold of 0.05' means the average metric value must be greater than 0.05.

- 'gardeners of code' is a metaphor for developers;
- 'algorithmic seeds' represents the algorithms they create;
- 'found fertile ground' implies that the algorithm has been accessed;
- 'specific cultivator' refers to the user with user_id = 1.

sql:
SELECT name
FROM algorithms
WHERE algorithm_id NOT IN (SELECT algorithm_id FROM benchmarks WHERE benchmark_name IS NOT NULL);
